.TH "__iucv_message_receive" 9 "__iucv_message_receive" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__iucv_message_receive \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __iucv_message_receive
.BI "(struct iucv_path *path "  ","
.BI "struct iucv_message *msg "  ","
.BI "u8 flags "  ","
.BI "void *buffer "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "size_t *residual "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "path" 12
address of iucv path structure
.IP "msg" 12
address of iucv msg structure
.IP "flags" 12
how the message is received (IUCV_IPBUFLST)
.IP "buffer" 12
address of data buffer or address of struct iucv_array
.IP "size" 12
length of data buffer
.IP "residual" 12
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function receives messages that are being sent to you over
established paths. This function will deal with RMDATA messages
embedded in struct iucv_message as well.

Locking:     no locking

Returns the result from the CP IUCV call.
